.<br /><br />One reason for that is that historically we've seen devices that<br />simply go crazy - to the point of simply stopping to respond to<br />anything - when you ask for pages that Windows doesn't ask for.<br /><br />It's especially common on USB storage, but it happens elsewhere too.<br />The device firmware simply hasn't ever been tested in that situation,<br />and it's buggy.<br /><br />So I don't mind the patch per se, but I think it's potentially way<br />more dangerous than it looks.<br /><br />                    Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
